<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">bluish marble</rs> columnar <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs>, broken below (height <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.45</measure>. diam. <measure dim="diameter" type="length">0.55</measure>).</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p><measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.05-0.06</measure>;  ll.9, 4, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.065</measure>; elongated and elegantly cut.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date notAfter="0388" exact="both" cert="low" notBefore="0385">A.D. 385/388</date> (<rs type="criteria">prosopography</rs>).</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<lg><lb n="1"/><l><g type="leaf"/> <rs type="subject" key="boule"><w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="βουλή">βουλὴ</w></rs> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w> <w lemma="πᾶς">πᾶσι</w> <w lemma="προσηνής">προς<lb n="2" type="worddiv"/>ηνέα</w> <w lemma="ὅδε">τόνδε</w> <persName type="aphrodisian" key="Menander1" full="yes"><name reg="Μένανδρος">Μένανδρον</name></persName></l><lb n="3"/><l><w lemma="πολύς">πολλῶν</w> <w lemma="ἀντί">ἀντ'</w> <w lemma="ἀγαθός">ἀγαθῶν</w><lb n="4"/><w lemma="ἵστημι">στῆσεν</w> <w lemma="ἀμείβομαι">ἀμειβομένη</w></l><lb n="5"/><l><w lemma="ὅς">ὃς</w> <w lemma="μέγας">μεγάλῃ</w> <w lemma="χαρίεις">χαρίεντα</w> <rs type="subject" key="city"><w lemma="πόλις">πόλι</w></rs><lb n="6"/><w lemma="θρεπτήριος">θρεπτήρια</w> <w lemma="τίς">τίνων</w></l><lb n="7"/><l><w lemma="δασμός">δασμοὺς</w> <w lemma="πραύνω">πρηΰνας</w> <w lemma="πᾶς">πᾶσιν</w><lb n="8"/><w lemma="τίθημι">ἔθηκε</w> <w lemma="φάος">φάος</w> <g type="leaf"/></l>
</lg>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>The Council, in exchange for many benefits, set up this <supplied reason="subaudible">statue of</supplied> Menandros, who was affable to all, and who, making a welcome repayment for his rearing to the great city, moderated <supplied reason="subaudible">her</supplied> tribute, and established light for all.</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="III.22">III.22</xref>.</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p><rs type="found"><rs type="monuList" key="HadrBath">Hadrianic Baths</rs>: '<foreign lang="fr">Galerie de l'Est—Partie S<supplied reason="abbreviation">ud</supplied></foreign>' (Boulanger); lying in the southern stretch of the west portico of the South Agora.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation" cert="low">Unknown</rs>. <rs type="lastLocation">Findspot (1973).</rs>. </p></div>





<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Excavated by the <rs type="visitor" key="mendel">French expedition</rs> in <date value="1905" notBefore="1905" notAfter="1905" exact="both">1905</date>, and copied by A. <rs type="visitor" key="boulanger">Boulanger</rs> in <date value="1913" notBefore="1913" notAfter="1913" exact="both">1913</date> (notebook A, 49 no. 1, whence B, 10-11, no. 9); copied by <rs type="visitor" key="robert">J. and L. Robert</rs> in <date value="1946" notBefore="1946" notAfter="1946" exact="both">1946</date>; recorded by the NYU expedition.</p>
</div>

